%% EXPLANATION:
%% Restructured the three SOX checkpoints to match the requested placement: (1) identity pre-screening now explicitly gates before the credit check, (2) a new risk scoring validation checkpoint was added after Finance performs risk scoring and routing—preserving the existing risk-based and expedited path logic untouched—and (3) the access control review remains post-provisioning. Five numbered documentation gates were added as note artifacts at request intake (#1), risk assessment (#2), approval justification (#3), audit logging at provisioning (#4), and closure/dossier assembly (#5), each attached to the owning participant rather than inline in the flow. Every major decision point and gate now carries a full RACI label (Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, Informed) as separate note annotations. No existing sequence flow arrows or business logic were removed or rerouted.